    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - POWER STEERING PUMP: VICKERS (LUK) V10NF AND V20NF - TEST PROCEDURES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>TEST PROCEDURES</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s05005s_28.xml" xrefid="hl0500501">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>
                to determine the specific test values for the steering pump to be tested.
            </para>
            <para>Install the analyzer in the steering system (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500507">Figure 7</hotlnk>). Place the thermometer in the reservoir. Run the engine and
                operate steering system until the power steering fluid temperature stabilizes at 160 degrees to 200
                degrees F (71 degrees to 93 degrees C).
                <emph type="bold">All tests should be performed at this temperature.</emph>
                Verify that the engine idle speed is set to specifications. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s05005s_28.xml" xrefid="hl0500501">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500507" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500507" filename="../figg05/G0500507.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Install Analyzer in Steering System</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. STEERING PUMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. THERMOMETER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RESERVOIR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. STEERING GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FLOW METER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. PRESSURE GAUGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. LOAD VALVE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
